(977, 'HIRESr, HIRESb', 1, 'Nasmyth focus', 'optical, ', 0.300000, 9, 1.000000, 9, '', '', '', '', 0, '', 0, 0, 0, '', 'HIRES is a grating cross-dispersed, echelle spectrograph.\r\n\r\nFor further information:\r\nhttp://www2.keck.hawaii.edu/inst/hires/'),
(978, 'LRIS Low Resolution Imaging Spectrometer', 8, 'Cassegrain focus', 'optical, ', 0.000000, 1, 0.000000, 1, '0.135 arcsec per pixel', 'R~300-5000', '', '6 × 7.8 arcmin', 0, '', 0, 0, 0, '', 'http://www2.keck.hawaii.edu/inst/lris/\r\n\r\nBeamsplitters separate the light between two arms. The red and blue cameras may be operated simultaneously, and together they may acquire spectra covering a 3200-10,000 Angstroms wavelength range.\r\n\r\nThe field of view in both modes of operation is 6×7.8 arcmin. The red camera uses a mosaic of two LBNL 2k x 4k fully depleted, high resistivity CCD detectors. The blue camera has a mosaic of 2 2Kx4K Marconi CCDs.\r\n\r\nThe standard imaging filters include the UBVGRI passbands plus a small number of narrowband imaging filters.\r\n\r\nSpectroscopy can be performed using a standard complement of longslits of various widths, or in multi-object mode, by using designed slitmasks which are milled on-site. An assortment of gratings (red side) and grisms (blue side) yield resolutions ranging from R=300-5,000, with peak system efficiencies of ~50%.\r\n\r\nAn optional polarimeter module enables spectropolarimetry. \r\n\r\n'),
(979, 'OSIRIS near-infrared integral field spectrograph', 1, '', 'infrared (IR), ', 9.900000, 9, 25.000000, 9, '', 'R~3800', '', '', 0, '2048x2048', 0, 0, 0, '', 'http://www2.keck.hawaii.edu/inst/osiris/\r\n\r\nThe instrument uses a lenslet array to sample a small rectangular patch of the sky at resolutions approaching the diffraction limit of the 10-m Keck Telescope. \r\n\r\nOSIRIS will provide moderate spectral resolution (R~3800), and full broadband (z, J, H, and K) spectral coverage at over 1000 spatial locations in the AO-corrected field. \r\n\r\nThe integral field design makes optimal use of new large-format (2048x2048) infrared arrays, and is well matched to the compact nature of AO targets.'),
(980, 'DEIMOS DEep Imaging Multi-Object Spectrograph', 1, 'Nasmyth focus', 'optical, ', 4000.000000, 7, 9000.000000, 7, '', 'up to R~6000', '', '81.5 X 81.5 arcmin', 0, '8000X8000', 0, 0, 0, '', 'http://www2.keck.hawaii.edu/inst/deimos/\r\n\r\nDEIMOS (DEep Imaging Multi-Object Spectrograph) is a visible-wavelength, faint-object, multi-slit imaging spectrograph.\r\n\r\nAvailable observing modes include direct imaging, long-slit spectroscopy (generous slit length spanning 16.6 arcmin on sky), and multi-slit spectroscopy of 100+ resolved targets per mask in conventional mode or 1000+ point-source targets per mask with narrow-band filters.'),
(981, 'NIRC-2 near-infrared instrument', 8, 'Left Nasmyth platform', 'Near-infrared (NIR)', 1.000000, 9, 5.000000, 9, '0.00994/0.01982/0.03968 arcsec per pixel', '', '', '10x10/20x20/40x40 arcsec', 0, '1024x1024', 0.25, 0, 0, 'InSb Aladdin-3 array', 'http://www2.keck.hawaii.edu/inst/nirc2/\r\n\r\nNIRC2 has imaging, spectrographic and coronagraphic capabilities.\r\n\r\nFilters: J,H,K,Ks,Kp,Lp,Ms,H2,FeII\r\nSlits: 10,20,30,40,60,80,120,and 160 milliarcsec\r\nCoronagraphic spots: circular: 100,150,200,300,400,600,800,1000,1500,2000 mas'),
(982, 'NIRSPEC- Near-Infrared Spectrometer', 1, '', 'Near-infrared (NIR)', 0.950000, 9, 5.500000, 9, '', 'R~25000/10800/2500', '', '', 0, '1024x1024', 0, 0, 0, '', 'http://www2.keck.hawaii.edu/inst/nirspec/\r\n\r\nNIRSPEC is a cyrogenic cross-dispersed echelle spectrograph designed for Keck II. It can be used with or without AO. The instrument is optimized as a high-resolution spectrograph with resolving power R (=λ/Δλ) =25,000 (12 km/s) for a slit width of 0.43 arcseconds (3 pixels).\r\n\r\nNIRSPEC has 3 detectors: a standard CCD camera for acquisition and offset guiding, a 1-2.5 μm near-infrared "slit-viewing" camera - the SCAM, and the primary 1024 x 1024 IR array for the spectrograph itself. '),
(983, 'ESI multi-mode spectrograph and imager', 8, 'Cassegrain focus', 'optical, ', 0.390000, 9, 1.100000, 9, '0.1542 arcsec per pixel', '', '', '3 arcminutes', 0, '2048x4096', 0, 0, 0, 'MIT-Lincoln Labs', 'http://www2.keck.hawaii.edu/inst/esi/\r\n\r\nThere are two distinct spectroscopic modes: a medium-resolution echellette mode with prism cross dispersion; and a high-throughput mode using prism dispersion only. The spectrograph modes will cover the full wavelength range (3900 to 11,000 Å) in a single exposure with a velocity resolution of ~10-15 km/sec/pixel. \r\n\r\nThe low-resolution, prism-only mode provides the same spectral range, multi-object capability, and high throughput. \r\n\r\nESI also provides an imaging mode with a field of view of 3.0 arc-minutes. \r\n\r\nAn Epps refracting camera and a single 2K x 4K detector are used for all three modes.'),
