(1856, 'GMOS - Gemini Multi-Object Spectrograph', 8, '', 'optical, ', 360.000000, 8, 940.000000, 8, '0.073 arcsec per pixel', '', '', '330 arcsec x 330 arcsec', 0, '', 0, 0, 0, '', 'GMOS is a multi-object, long-slit and IFU spectrograph and imager. \r\n\r\nThree types of spectroscopy are possible with its selection of gratings:\r\n-Long-slit spectroscopy, which covers the full extent of the CCD package (3 x 2048 pixels) with two small gaps.\r\n-Multi-object spectroscopy, which uses custom-designed, laser-milled masks.\r\n-Integral field spectroscopy, which uses 0.2 arcsec fibers covering a 35 square arcsec field of view.\r\n\r\nGMOS can perform broad band imaging (using the SDSS filter system) or narrow-band imaging using select filters. For imaging, the field of view is 5.5 arcmin x 5.5 arcmin. \r\n\r\nFor further details about this instrument see: http://www.gemini.edu/node/10625'),
(1857, 'T-ReCS - Thermal-Region Camera Spectrograph', 8, '', 'Mid-infrared (MIR), ', 8.000000, 9, 26.000000, 9, '0.09 arcsec per pixel', 'R~100-1000', '', '', 0, '', 0, 0, 0, '', 'T-ReCS is a mid-infrared imager and long-slit spectrograph. When combined with Gemini''s fast tip/tilt compensating secondary mirror, T-ReCS will yield nearly diffraction-limited 10-µm images under most natural seeing conditions. \r\n\r\nT-ReCS is capable of imaging in the 8–26 µm range as follows:\r\n-Broad-band (N, Q) and Narrow-band Filter Imaging\r\n-Pixel size = 0.09" (fixed)\r\n-Field of view = 28.8"×21.6"\r\n-Number of filters: currently 20, capacity for 24\r\n-Occulting bar available for imaging (2" wide)\r\n\r\nT-ReCS is capable of spectroscopy with R~100 - 1000 in the 8–26 µm range as follows:\r\n-Low resolution long-slit spectroscopy: R ~ 100 near 10 µm, R ~ 80 near 20 µm\r\n-Medium long-slit spectroscopy: R ~ 1000 near 10 µm\r\n-Pixel size in spatial direction = 0.09" (fixed)\r\n-Slit length = 21.6"\r\n-Slit widths = 0.21" to 1.32"\r\n-Low-Res Dispersion at 10 µm = 0.02213 µm/pix, delta lambda = 7.1 µm (entire N band) across detector\r\n-Low-Res Dispersion at 20 µm = 0.033 µm/pix, delta lambda = 10.6 µm (entire Q band)\r\n-Hi-Res Dispersion at 10 µm = 0.0019 µm/pix, delta lambda = 0.6 µm\r\n\r\nFor further details about this instrument see:\r\nhttp://www.gemini.edu/sciops/instruments/trecs'),
(1858, 'NICI - Near-Infrared Coronagraphic Imager', 6, '', 'Near-infrared (NIR), ', 1.000000, 9, 5.000000, 9, '18 mas per pixel', '', '', '18 arcsec x 18 arcsec', 0, '1024 x 1024', 0, 0, 0, '1024x1024 ALADDIN InSb array', 'NICI combines an 85-element curvature adaptive optics system, a dedicated Lyot coronagraph, and a specialized dual-channel camera into a single instrument optimized to detect large Jovian-type planets around nearby stars.\r\n\r\nFor further details about this instrument, see:\r\nhttp://www.gemini.edu/sciops/instruments/nici/?q=sciops/instruments/nici'),
