(2049, 'FLAMINGOS - Florida Infrared Imaging Multi-object Spectrograph', 8, '', 'infrared, ', 0.900000, 9, 2.500000, 9, '0.316', 'R ~ 1000-1900', '', '600 x 600', 0, '2048 x 2048', 0, 0, 0, 'HgCdTe', 'http://www.noao.edu/kpno/manuals/flmn/flmn.user.html\r\n\r\nFLAMINGOS is a wide-field IR imager and multi-slit spectrometer. \r\nThe imaging mode is provided by a fairly conventional optical train, consisting of a refractive collimator, filters, cold stop and a camera, which images the focal plane onto a 2K x 2K HgCdTe detector.\r\nThe filters available for imaging are J, H, K and Ks.\r\n\r\nThe spectroscopic mode is provided by a cold slit mask placed at the telescope focal plane, and by a grism placed after the cold stop. The slit masks are mounted in a wheel in a separate MOS dewar in front of the camera section at the telescope focal plane. The MOS wheel can accommodate 11 slit masks (enough for 2 - 3 nights of typical observing), in addition to permanently-mounted long slits. At present, there are two grisms covering the JH and HK atmospheric windows which provide two-pixel R ~ 1000 - 1800, depending on the wavelength and filter/grism combination. \r\n\r\nSingle or multi-slit capability with the 4-m Mayall Telescope.\r\n\r\nInstr. Support: Dick Joyce, Rm. 159, x8323, (520) 318-8323, rjoyce@noao.edu\r\n\r\nInstr. Support: Ron Probst, Rm. 49, x8268, (520) 318-8268, rprobst@noao.edu'),
(2050, 'R-C CCD Spectrograph', 8, 'Ritchey-Chrétien', '', 550.000000, 7, 4700.000000, 7, '0.69', 'R ~ 300-5000', '', '324', 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 'T2KA/LB1A CCD', 'http://www.noao.edu/kpno/manuals/l2mspect/'),
(2051, 'CCD Echelle Spectrograph', 1, '', 'ultraviolet, optical, ', 0.000000, 1, 0.000000, 1, '', '', '', '', 0, '', 0, 0, 0, '', 'http://www.noao.edu/kpno/manuals/echman/\r\n\r\nThe Kitt Peak 4-meter echelle spectrograph is a versatile instrument capable of high resolution (<= 80,000 or >= 0.07Å) over a wide range of wavelengths. Its two-dimensional format (cover figure) is ideal for array detectors. Cross dispersion gratings are available (table 6) to provide efficient spectral coverage from 3000 to 10,000 Å. The echelle spectrograph is used with CCDs to obtain spectra of stars as faint as mv ~ 15 or even fainter, depending on the resolution and signal to noise required.'),
(2052, 'MARS - Multi-Aperture Red Spectometer', 1, '', '', 3400.000000, 7, 10000.000000, 7, '', '8-30 Å', '', '', 0, '', 0, 0, 0, '', 'http://www.noao.edu/kpno/manuals/mars/mars_man2.html'),
(2053, 'FLAMINGOS - Florida Infrared Imaging Multi-object Spectrograph', 8, '', 'infrared, ', 0.900000, 9, 2.500000, 9, '0.606', 'R ~ 1000-1800', '', '1200 x 1200', 0, '2048 x 2048', 0, 0, 0, 'HgCdTe', 'http://www.noao.edu/kpno/manuals/flmn/flmn.user.html\r\n\r\nFLAMINGOS is a wide-field IR imager and multi-slit spectrometer. \r\nThe imaging mode is provided by a fairly conventional optical train, consisting of a refractive collimator, filters, cold stop and a camera, which images the focal plane onto a 2K x 2K HgCdTe detector.\r\nThe filters available for imaging are J, H, K and Ks.\r\n\r\nThe spectroscopic mode is provided by a cold slit mask placed at the telescope focal plane, and by a grism placed after the cold stop. The slit masks are mounted in a wheel in a separate MOS dewar in front of the camera section at the telescope focal plane. The MOS wheel can accommodate 11 slit masks (enough for 2 - 3 nights of typical observing), in addition to permanently-mounted long slits. At present, there are two grisms covering the JH and HK atmospheric windows which provide two-pixel R ~ 1000 - 1800, depending on the wavelength and filter/grism combination. \r\n\r\nLong-slit capability only with the 2.1-m Telescope.\r\n\r\n\r\nInstr. Support: Dick Joyce, Rm. 159, x8323, (520) 318-8323, rjoyce@noao.edu\r\n\r\nInstr. Support: Ron Probst, Rm. 49, x8268, (520) 318-8268, rprobst@noao.edu\r\n'),
(2210, 'ST9XE', 5, 'Prime focus', 'optical, ', 0.000000, 1, 0.000000, 1, '1.45', '', '', '745x745', 0, '512x512', 1, 1200, 0, 'KAF-0261E', ''),
(2212, '90Prime', 5, '', 'optical, ', 0.000000, 1, 0.000000, 1, '0.45', '', '', '4176 x 4176', 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 'Four 4k x 4k CCDs', 'http://cameras.itl.arizona.edu/index.html?90Prime.html\r\n\r\n90Prime is a prime focus wide-field facility imager for the Steward Observatory 90" telescope. \r\n\r\nThe optical design includes a four element corrector and six position filter wheel. \r\n\r\nThe focal plane array is a mosaic of four 4k x 4k CCDs which have been processed for back illumination by the University of Arizona Imaging Technology Laboratory. The camera provides an imaging area of 1.0 square degree on the four CCDs. The edge-to-edge field-of-view including the inter-CCD spacing is 1.16° x 1.16° with a plate scale of 30.2"/mm or 0.45"/pixel.'),
