(2247, 'ALFOSC - Andalucia Faint Object Spectrograph and Camera', 8, '', 'UV-optical, ', 280.000000, 8, 2250.000000, 8, '0.19', '', 'linear and/or circular modes available', '6''.4 x 6''.4', 0, '2048 x 2048(+4)', 0, 0, 0, 'E2V 2kx2k CCD42-40 nimo back illuminated', 'http://www.not.iac.es/instruments/alfosc/\r\nALFOSC can be used for UV-optical imaging, polarimetry and low-resolution spectroscopy.\r\n\r\nALFOSC spectroscopy 	from 3200-11000Å, with dispersion (Å/pixel) of 0.26-13.7 for long slit (5''), and 0.4 in echelle mode (slit length 8"). Spectropolarimetry and Multi Object (MOS) mode also available.\r\n\r\nFor polarimetry:\r\nALFOSC FAPOL+ calcite: Various optical filters, FoV 140" diameter, modes: linear and/or circular (also for spectropolarimetry)\r\nALFOSC polaroid: Various optical filters, FoV 6''.4 x 6''.4, mode: linear, for extended targets.\r\nALFOSC +WeDoWo: Various optical filters, mode: linear 	'),
(2248, 'NOTCam - Nordic Optical Telescope near-infrared Camera and spectrograph', 8, '', 'infrared, ', 0.800000, 9, 2.500000, 9, '', '', '', '', 0, '1024 x 1024', 0, 0, 0, 'HgCdTe', 'http://www.not.iac.es/instruments/notcam/\r\nNOTCam - NIR imaging and low-resolution spectroscopy \r\n\r\nNOTCam is capable of:\r\nWide field imaging (4''×4'' @ 0.234"/pixel)\r\nHigh resolution imaging (80"×80" @ 0.078"/pixel)\r\nLow-resolution (R = 2500) WF-cam spectroscopy (Y,J,H,K) \r\nMedium-resolution (R = 5500) HR-cam spectroscopy (J,H,K)\r\n\r\nIn the future, expected to upgrade NOTCam with Wollaston prisms for imaging polarimetry and spectro-polarimetry. '),
(2249, 'FIES - FIbre-fed Echelle Spectrograph ', 1, '', 'optical, ', 370.000000, 8, 730.000000, 8, '', '', '', '', 0, '', 0, 0, 0, '', 'http://www.not.iac.es/instruments/fies/\r\nFIES - High-resolution, high-stability optical spectroscopy\r\n\r\nThe currently installed fiber bundle contains a high-res 1.3 arcsec fibre offering a spectral resolution of R=67000. This bundle also provides two 1.3 arcsec fibres giving R=46000 (med-res), and a fibre with a larger entrance aperture of 2.5 arcsec but a lower spectral resolution (R=25000, low-res). '),
(2250, 'MOSCA - MOSaic CAmera ', 5, '', 'UV-optical, ', 0.000000, 1, 0.000000, 1, '0.217"/pixel on sky (2x2 binning)', '', '', '7''.7 x 7''.7', 0, '', 0.5, 0, 0, '4 2048x2048 Loral-Lesser thinned CCDs (CCD7/10/11/12)', 'http://www.not.iac.es/instruments/mosaic/\r\n\r\nMOSCA - High-resolution, high-efficiency UV-optical imaging\r\n\r\nFilters: Full field of view with 100 mm filter, 60mm round filter FOV about 5''25" (diameter) Available filters: (100 mm) Bessell UBVRI, SDSS u''g''r''i''z'';(90mm) Strömgren uvby, H-beta wide, narrow (see filters at NOT).'),
(2251, 'StanCam - Standby CCD Camera', 5, '', '', 0.000000, 1, 0.000000, 1, '0.176', '', '', '3'' x 3''', 0, '1024 x 1024', 0, 0, 0, 'TEK 1024x1024 back-side illuminated thinned CCD', 'http://www.not.iac.es/instruments/stancam/\r\n\r\nStanCam is mounted in a folded Cassegrain focus and kept cool using CryoTiger. It is used as an optical imaging instrument when ALFOSC or MOSCA is not mounted and also as a FIES fiber viewer.'),
