(14, 'Chandrayaan-1', 11, NULL, '2008-10-22', '0000-00-00', 'http://www.isro.gov.in/Chandrayaan/htmls/home.htm', 'The Chandrayaan-1 mission is India''s first scientific mission to the Moon, aimed at high-resolution remote sensing in visible, near infrared (NIR), low energy X-rays and high-energy X-ray regions. Specifically the objectives are:\r\n- To prepare a three-dimensional atlas (with high spatial and altitude resolution of 5-10 m) of both near and far side of the moon.\r\n	\r\n- To conduct chemical and mineralogical mapping of the entire lunar surface for distribution of mineral and chemical elements such as Magnesium, Aluminum, Silicon, Calcium, Iron and Titanium as well as high atomic number elements such as Radon, Uranium & Thorium with high spatial resolution.', '2011-03-03 03:32:02', '2012-07-25 13:02:34', '', ''),
