(3449, 'RT-22', 10, 0, 1, 22.000000, '9.525', 1, 'radiowave, ', 0.000000, 1, 0.000000, 1, 'Further information on this instrument available under http://crao.crimea.ua/rt22/enviroment_en.htm and under http://quake.stanford.edu/~crao/craoinfo/rt22.html \r\n\r\n***\r\n\r\nBasic trends of researches (with wavelength regions included) (as cited by http://crao.crimea.ua/rt22/enviroment_en.htm ):\r\n\r\n1.      VLBI observations\r\n\r\nInternational VLBI-observations within the framework of astrophysical, geophysical and radio-location projects at frequencies 326, 612 MHz, 1.6, 2.3, 5.0, 8.4 and 22 GHz. These observations are supported by the hydrogen frequency standard with the stability 10-14 in the interval 1-24 hours and registration systems Мark-5 and NRTV.\r\n \r\n2.      Multi-frequency monitoring of active galactic nuclei (AGNs).\r\n\r\nThe regular monitoring is carried out at frequencies 22.2 and 36.8 GHz.\r\n \r\n3.      Researches of the solar and stellar activity.\r\n \r\nAt the station the observations of the Sun and stars are carried out at frequencies 8.6, 10.7, 13.3, 15.4, 22.2 and 36.8 GHz. I (intensity) and V (circular polarization) Stokes parameters are registered.\r\n \r\n4.      Observations of molecular lines in millimeter range\r\n \r\nObservations of molecular lines of maser sources, star forming region and others, intragalactic objects at frequencies 1.6 - 1.8 GHz (ON masers), 4.6 - 5.1 GHz (ON masers), 22.2 GHz (Н2О masers) and in the range from 85 - 115 GHz (thermal radiation of various molecules). '),
(3450, 'RT-3', 10, 0, 1, 3.000000, '1.25', 1, 'radiowave, ', 0.000000, 1, 0.000000, 1, 'Further information on this telescope available under http://quake.stanford.edu/~crao/craoinfo/rt22.html'),
(3451, '2.6m Shajn Reflector', 17, 0, 0, 0.000000, '', 1, 'optical, ', 0.000000, 1, 0.000000, 1, '- Observations are possible in Primary, Nasmyth, Cassegrain and Coude foci.\r\n\r\n- A new polarimeter will replace the old one, expected in 2013.\r\n\r\n- A new primary focus low-resolution spectrograph is at the conceptual design stage.\r\n\r\n- Further information on this telescope available under http://www.crao.crimea.ua/~dshakh/\r\n'),
